notes: Day number 6!!! Tried to take a risk today, NY open shot up with no retest at all of the ORB. We got up to a point of consolidation i had conviction it was going to retrace back down to the mid point, It did not. I ended up taking a loss on a short, I panicked and flipped my position at 7002 and went long until 10:16am Where my trailed Stop ended up getting hit. I think there is opportunity for these additional entries after the ORB but we need a lot of practice.

Day number 5!!!! Cant believe we have another win! Today we had a decent amount of news, We blew up past the ORB before NY open, We eventually retraced back down and respected the orb multiple times so i went ahead and put a small risk 3 contract in, risked 20 dollars per contract. We went back up close to session highs and i actually meant to clip off one contract but i sold all 3 for a decent profit, Happy accident i wanted to be out of this all together by 8am for the News anyways! Look for smaller opportunities dude, We don't have to go for hundreds of dollars per contract. Arguably we could have left the small 60 dollar stop loss and let it ride a little higher but for a news day i am happy.

notes: Day number 4!!! This one was wild, I had a perfect Retest at the midpoint and a really good entry. Right after entering i hopped in a Stream and heard NQ was completely dumping when i just longed ES... Es did some very bad and choppy price action dropping all the way past the orb close to my 12 point stop and would retrace back up to around 15 points above. I tried to be paitent and see if we could do a little better but after we retraced to my mid point again and stalled out again 15 points up i clipped on contract off while in a meeting at work waited a little longer and basically the same thing happened again so i clipped the last two contracts off securing a win. EOD UPDATE: Price did not do really any better later in the day, I am very happy with my exit.

notes: Day Three!!!! We finally have a win, Today i waited until NY open to wait for a better confirmation. Entered a few points above the mid point which seemed needed but it actually wasn't. We tested the midpoint wicked down twice but never closed below. Once again my SL discipline hurt me, I lost on a good bit of profit on two contracts because i moved my SL and a random wick came and knocked me out while the market is still pumping up. I made a pretty big mistake by allowing my SL to sell a third contract that i did not actually have so we lost almost 20$ on that mistake.

notes: Day Number two!!! Trying to keep the hype up. Saw a Retest at like 6:30AM, I think the main failure point on this trade was some unknown news over the weekend about a US > Venezuela Bombing. I sized up to the Eval Position size of 3 contracts. Got stopped out at my 12 point loss. Going forward for all Monday Trades i need to review the weekend news Sunday night, Baby girls idea. Wondering if i need to wait until a little closer to new york open to jump in instead of so early. Hard to tell what's enough volume to get in before NY open.

notes: DAY NUMBER ONE BAAAAABBBYYYYYYY: Took my first trade on the Eval today. We had some decent price action pre market open, 3-6 hundred contracts per 1 minute candle. Took the short off the midpoint, Ran down just about to TP, We quickly reversed back up past the midpoint and touched my SL. I am mad because I listened to AI and allowed to scare me and set my SL lower than what my Strategy says to do. I would have hit all targets perfectly had i followed the 12 point SL target instead of Ai's suggestion of 1% of my 2k draw down limit.
